<!DOCTYPE chapter PUBLIC "-//OASIS//DTD DocBook XML V4.5//EN" "http://www.oasis-open.org/docbook/xml/4.5/docbookx.dtd">
<chapter id="faces.installation">
	<title>Installation</title>
	<para> Most features of Seam Reports are installed automatically by including the
		seam-reports.jar and seam-reports-api.jar in the web application library folder. If you are
		using <ulink url="http://maven.apache.org/">Maven</ulink> as your build tool, you can add
		the following dependency to your pom.xml file: </para>
	<programlisting role="XML"><![CDATA[<dependency>
	<groupId>org.jboss.seam.reports</groupId>
	<artifactId>seam-reports</artifactId>
	<version>${seam-reports-version}</version>
</dependency>]]></programlisting>
	<tip>
		<para>Replace ${seam-reports-version} with the most recent or appropriate version of Seam
			Reports.</para>
	</tip>
</chapter>
